BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Events
DESCRIPTION:Do you know how you can still see animals in the winter? During
  this short hike we teach you about tracks\, tree rubbings\, and scat to he
 lp you know what animals active in the winter months. Meet at the Deer Run 
 Shelter to begin our hike on Trail 9.
DTEND:20260220T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260317T230318Z
DTSTART:20260220T190000Z
GEO:39.286051;-86.726529
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Deer Run Shelter 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Winter Animal Evidence\, McCormick's Creek State Park
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51410885543532
URL:https://events.in.gov/event/winter-animal-evidence
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Events
DESCRIPTION:Did you know during Brumation turtle hibernate under the frozen
  lake? Turtles extract oxygen bubbles from the water to survive three month
 s under the ice. Come create your own frozen bubbles at the Nature Center. 
 The outside temperature must be under 32 degrees to make the bubbles work. 
 We will still have fun turtle facts for you to learn.
DTEND:20260221T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260317T230318Z
DTSTART:20260221T190000Z
GEO:39.286051;-86.726529
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Nature Center
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Turtle's Winter Bubbles\, McCormick's Creek State Park
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51410984822844
URL:https://events.in.gov/event/turtles-winter-bubbles
END:VEVENT
