DESCRIPTION:Birds do not have hands or teeth. How do they eat? With their b
 eaks! Birds’ beaks have adapted to allow them to be specialists in their fi
 elds. You will put their beak through difficult tasks like finding food. Th
 is lab is held in the program room at the Nature Center.
