DESCRIPTION:Come see our local Red-eared Slider hunt for fish. This program
  is held at the Canyon Inn.  \n\nNature Center is open every day from 10 am
 -5 pm EDT in May-October\n\nClosed on Tuesdays and Wendesdays November-Apri
 l\n\nUpcoming programs can be seen by visiting on.in.gov/mccormickscreek\n\
 nOur interpretive programs are designed to entertain and enrich folks of al
 l ages. Children under 12 must have an adult with them at the programs.\n\n
 Registration is not required for programs (unless stated). All our programs
  are free (unless otherwise noted). They are open to the public after payin
 g the park entrance fee.\n\nAll our Interpretive programs are listed in Eas
 tern Daylight Savings Time.\n\n*Note that during peak visitation times\, en
 try into our park might be delayed. The drive to the Nature Center can take
  8 minutes. Please plan accordingly. *\n\nIf you need more information\, ca
 ll 812-829-2235 ext. 2
